# patterns/ starts empty
#
# One file per play that's worked more than once — your reusable playbooks.
# Filename = the pattern, slugified. Example: static-dashboards-over-spas.md
#
# The dashboard README and the Chart.js ADR forward-reference
# [[patterns/static-dashboards-over-spas]] — a dashed node in Obsidian until you
# fill it in. When you next reach for that pattern, ask Claude:
#   "Write the pattern entry brain/patterns/static-dashboards-over-spas.md.
#    Add [[wikilinks]] back to the projects that used it."
#
# This .gitkeep exists only so the empty folder survives a git clone. Delete it
# once you have real entries.
